  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Athlete receives a light medicine ball while moving and finishes in a balanced deceleration stick before returning it.","setup":["Pair athletes by size, skill, maturity, and ability to follow stop commands.","Define the athlete role, partner role, allowed contact/resistance, and the stop word before the first rep.","Set safe spacing and clear the area of obstacles; use cones, mat, line, band, or ball as needed."],"execution_steps":["Athlete performs: Athlete receives a light medicine ball while moving and finishes in a balanced deceleration stick before returning it.","Partner supplies only the agreed cue, toss, resistance, support, or perturbation and stays attentive to the athlete''s posture.","Reset after each rep or short work window, then switch roles so both partners receive the same quality exposure."],"coach_cues":["Talk before force.","Match the partner, do not beat the partner.","Clean rep, clean reset.","Stop on sloppy spacing or posture."],"common_faults":["Partner adds too much force or surprise","Athlete rushes the rep to win instead of solving the movement problem","Spacing drifts and the pair loses a safe lane","Breath holding, shrugging, or trunk collapse under partner input","Perturbation becomes a challenge contest instead of controlled exposure"],"breathing_cues":["Exhale through effort or contact","Do not hold breath to survive partner force","Recover breathing before switching roles"],"quality_gate":"The rep counts only if both partners keep the agreed role, safe spacing, communication, posture, and controlled reset.","stop_signs":["Pain","dizziness","panic step","fall risk","partner surprise force","lost spacing","dropped implement near feet","speed or posture decay"]}'::jsonb,
